It is possible to stream videos with adaptive bit-rate, using Media Source Extensions. 

It is important to note that, videos must be in **streaming friendly format** (e.g. fMP4), otherwise we have to remux them; 

By the way, it may be challenging to split files right before key frames.

@Bullseye: You might forget to copy your other files. Your `loader\files\` is almost empty.

Can you load your file at http://127.0.0.1:18905/ ?
If you can, you might forget to copy all of your files.

@Bullseye: in `users.json`:
```
"1PE5GTgUjKVQuudoz4P1YCrmZPVXvZwRmR": {
  "auth_privatekey": "5..............",
```

@Bullseye: All you need to do is to download **ZeroMux Bundle** again. You don't need to reinstall ZeroNet unless you broke it last night.
[Download](127.0.0.1:43110/1CiDoBP8RiWziqiBGEd8tQMy66A6fmnw2V/big/bundle/), upload your file, copy `loader` folder, sign and publish.

If you can't find a peer, use [these](https://bit.no.com:43110/1PE5GTgUjKVQuudoz4P1YCrmZPVXvZwRmR) [ZeroNet](https://onlyzero.net/1PE5GTgUjKVQuudoz4P1YCrmZPVXvZwRmR) [gateways](https://zerogate.tk/1PE5GTgUjKVQuudoz4P1YCrmZPVXvZwRmR) to seed your site.
